                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "A medication has been prescribed for a client with hypoparathyroidism for management of hypocalcemia. The client arrives at the clinic for follow-up evaluation and complains of chronic constipation since beginning the medication. The nurse provides information to the client regarding measures to alleviate the constipation and determines that the client needs additional information when the client makes which statement?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nClients taking medications to treat hypocalcemia would be instructed to avoid the use of mineral oil as a laxative because mineral oil decreases vitamin D absorption, and vitamin D is needed to assist in the absorption of calcium. The remaining options are basic measures to alleviate constipation.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, measures to alleviate constipation. Note the strategic words, needs additional information. This phrasing indicates a negative event query and asks you to select an option that is an incorrect statement. Eliminate options 1, 2, and 3 because they are general and basic measures that will assist in alleviating constipation.",
                        "id": "908cac61d0d14f8ca4fe1bd87167f399",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
