                        "content": "A nurse is caring for a client with a diagnosis of hyperthyroidism. Laboratory studies are performed, and the serum calcium level is 12.0 mg/dL (3 mmol/L). Which medication would the nurse anticipate to be prescribed for the client?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe normal serum calcium level is 9 to 10.5 mg/dL (2.25 to 2.75 mmol/L). This client is experiencing hypercalcemia. Calcitonin, a thyroid hormone, decreases the plasma calcium level by increasing the incorporation of calcium into the bones, thus keeping it out of the serum. Calcium chloride and calcium gluconate are medications used for the treatment of tetany, which occurs from acute hypocalcemia. In hypercalcemia, large doses of vitamin D need to be avoided.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, treatment for a serum calcium level of 12.0 mg/dL (3 mmol/L). First, you need to determine that the client is experiencing hypercalcemia. With this knowledge, you can easily eliminate options 2 and 3 because you would not administer medication that would add calcium to the body. Remembering that excessive vitamin D is a causative factor of hypercalcemia will assist in eliminating option 4.",
                        "id": "b300fbba339343ea896d44b6800cf677",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "71f0a72c0cc042af8b7d56f77de75b26",
                                "content": "\"I need to take this medication with food.\""
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "7dc9aab17a784409b9d04bf0994ffc79",
                                "content": "\"I need to take this medication at bedtime.\""
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "2af639de330a4dcd973173711e8d6189",
                                "content": "\"I would sit up for at least 30 minutes after taking this medication.\""
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "2a600053f8e34443abe04f3913588bf1",
                                "content": "\"I need to take this medication first thing in the morning on an empty stomach.\""
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "347613a46a5442afab2d6b540b3f3d3b",
                                "content": "\"I can pick a time to take this medication that best fits my lifestyle as long as I take it at the same time each day.\""
                            }
                        ],
