                        "type": "1",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The client with hyperparathyroidism is taking alendronate. Which statements by the client indicate understanding of the proper way to take this medication? Select all that apply.",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nAlendronate is a bisphosphonate used in hyperparathyroidism to inhibit bone loss and normalize serum calcium levels. Esophagitis is an adverse effect of primary concern in clients taking alendronate. For this reason, the client is instructed to take alendronate first thing in the morning with a full glass of water on an empty stomach, not to eat or drink anything else for at least 30 minutes after taking the medication, and to remain sitting upright for at least 30 minutes after taking it. A daily dosing schedule and a once-weekly dosing schedule are available for clients taking alendronate.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, the correct method to take alendronate. Recall that the primary concern with alendronate is esophagitis. Eliminate options 1 and 2 since taking with food and taking at bedtime will each place the client at increased risk of reflux. Eliminate option 5 because alendronate needs to be taken first thing in the morning on an empty stomach.",
                        "id": "c9b205251cb440408514a21769b1f73f",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    }
                ]
